ModFossa Ion Channel Simulator 
==============================

http://public.modfossa.here

Gareth Ferneyhough, University of Nevada, Reno. 
gareth.ferneyhough@gmail.com


Overview
---------

Simple three-state ion channel model using Sundials ODE Solver, 
Boost:Python and PyUblas

Build instructions
------------------

This requires Boost (including Boost:Python and Ublas), 
Sundials ODE Solver, and PyUblas. They are available here:

	https://computation.llnl.gov/casc/sundials/download/download.html
	http://www.boost.org/
	git clone http://git.tiker.net/trees/pyublas.git
	
To build, create a new directory called 'build' and invoke cmake from the
new build directory like so:

	cmake -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=../python ../CMake
	
This will generate makefiles in the build directory. You can change the install 
prefix if you wish. Then type the usual 'make' and 'make install'. You can build
documentation with 'make Documentation'.

Running
-------

Run 'run.py' in the 'Python' directory. Make sure libModFossa.so is in 
the same directory, or somewhere where Python can find it.